originalText.text: Be extremely cautious and aware if you insist on hiring this doctor for your gyn needs. She left my family members in the waiting room 1-2 hours beyond the end my operation without notifying them that my surgery had ended and reporting my condition. They were beyond worried and had to complain to the hospital advocate who called her and found her back at her office outside the hospital. At my post-surgical visit with her, I told her I had a little pain in an area and she merely shrugged her shoulders -- zero response -- not even a guess etc.  After the practice that she worked for let her go 6mos to a year later, I had already moved onto excellent care with another gyn.

originalText.text: Dr. Eden has been my physician for over 20 years and she is an excellent, compassionate doctor. As a practicing physician myself, I have complete trust and confidence in her clinical abilities. She is professional and at the same time, caring and uncrushed. In addition, she has seen both of my daughters. I recommend Dr. Eden without any reservations; any woman would be fortunate to have her level of expertise and care!

originalText.text: I have been with Dr Eden for a few years now and have always had the best experience with each visit. We had discussed and tried a few different options for treating post menopausal dryness and eventually settled on the laser option. This treatment was the best decision I made for myself. It’s painless, little downtime and has changed my life. I would recommend this to anybody suffering from dryness and pain.

originalText.text: While I only saw Dr. Eden once, so far, the experience brought me hope. Afters years of being tossed around by doctors, I feel I am being heard and that Dr. Eden really wants to help. She took her time (I was her last appointment) and made me feel extremely comfortable.
